  "text": "One difference between our model and the Lockwood model follows from the definition of compartments; within Simbiology compartments must be defined in terms of volume, whereas Lockwood's compartments are is in terms of mass [CITATION_1] . Thus, assumed density values were used to derive the compartment volume fractions listed in Table 1 . Other differences include the definition of organ compartments such as the brain from the richly perfused tissue compartment for some of our simulations as shown in Fig. 1 .",
